<div id="review_2032273484" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2032273484" />
    <a title="Erin Daniels" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/64221521-erin-daniels"><img alt="Erin Daniels" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1485877620p2/64221521.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2032273484?book_show_action=true">Jun 17, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Erin Daniels" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Erin Daniels" href="/user/show/64221521-erin-daniels">Erin Daniels</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/34227056-through-the-mind-s-eye">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2032273484" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8660707492280098126">Through The Mind&apos;s Eye was a powerful yet poignant exploration of struggle, addiction and how we pick up the pieces when things fall apart. I found the author&apos;s honesty to be inspirational because he was telling his truth, not necessarily claiming his experience was universal. However, I found little gems throughout the book that made me pause and think of my own life. You don&apos;t have to be in recovery to glean hope and insight from this book and the humor and straightforwardness of the text kept</span>
  <span id="freeText8660707492280098126" style="display:none">Through The Mind's Eye was a powerful yet poignant exploration of struggle, addiction and how we pick up the pieces when things fall apart. I found the author's honesty to be inspirational because he was telling his truth, not necessarily claiming his experience was universal. However, I found little gems throughout the book that made me pause and think of my own life. You don't have to be in recovery to glean hope and insight from this book and the humor and straightforwardness of the text kept me as engaged as if I were reading fiction. Well done!</span>
  <a data-text-id="8660707492280098126" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


